msgstr "Generally, it is difficult to obtain the electronic states of large molecules, such as proteins or peptide chains, using only a single-point calculation without any reference. We therefore first divide proteins into smaller fragments such as amino acid residues, and start calculations from the fragments. Using the results, we then further calculate larger peptide chains. The :num:`Fig. #qclosteps` shows the method overview:"

